Pre-Game Insights: Shohei Ohtani will see Yoshinobu Yamamoto face off against San Diego's Yu Darvish in Game 5.
It will be the first matchup of Japanese-born starting pitchers in Major League postseason history.
Darvish gave up one run and three hits over seven innings in the Padres' 10-2 win in Game 2.
Yamamoto has given up a combined 13 earned runs in three starts against the Padres this season.
The Dodgers used eight relievers to shut out the Padres and win 8-0 in Game 4.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Yamamoto is the highest paid pitcher in the majors with a $325 million, 12-year deal.
Freddie Freeman is expected to be back in the lineup after a sprained right ankle.
Miguel Rojas won’t be in the Dodgers’ starting lineup but will be available to pinch hit.
Jack Flaherty is in the discussion for the starting role.
